import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['price'] = pd.to_numeric(data['price'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='price', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['price'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['price'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of price?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='date', y='price', data=data)
    chart.axhline(y=data['price'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median Price: {:.2f}'.format(data['price'].median()))
    chart.legend()
    plt.title('What is the trend of price over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='symbol', y='price', data=data, ci=None)
    chart.axhline(y=data['price'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['price'].mean():.2f}")
    chart.set(xlabel='Symbol', ylabel='Price')
    chart.legend()
    return chart

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='date', kde=False, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['date'].min(), color='red', label=f'Min date: {data["date"].min().strftime("%Y-%m-%d")}')
    plt.axvline(data['date'].max(), color='green', label=f'Max date: {data["date"].max().strftime("%Y-%m-%d")}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of dates?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
